    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Emergency Window Exit Alarms</title>
        <para>Depending on which type, horizontal or vertical kick-out style window, the window exit alarms are removed
            by:
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four mounting screws securing the window mounting cover plates each side of the
                window assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the window from the window opening, remove any caulking seal that may remain in the
                window opening.
            </para>
            <figure id="f47004162" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/g47004162.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 162. Emergency Window Alarm Switch</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WINDOW SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. EMERGENCY WINDOW LATCH HANDLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. EMERGENCY WINDOW LOWER LOCK BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. EMERGENCY WINDOW AJAR WARNING SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. PASSENGER WINDOW LOWER FRAME</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove both sets of screws at each end of the window frame at the bottom (or side if
                vertically hinged) that hold the plunger switch in place.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the wire lead that is connected to the switch.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
